<title type="html"><![CDATA[11/19 (Thu.) Sleep quality / Early bird vs. Night owl (Host: Sherry Liao)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=446&amp;p=464#p464"><![CDATA[
<img class="smilies" src="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/images/smilies/icon_redface.gif" alt=":oops:" title="Embarrassed" /> ~<span style="color: #FF4040"> New Place ~ New Agenda~ New host <img class="smilies" src="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /> <br /><br />Thursday gathering is relocated to 丹堤咖啡, 台北市延平南路107號2樓 (MRT 西門站4號出口)<br /><br />New Agenda:<br />6:30-7:15 pm Free talk<br />7:15-7:50 pm Session 1 discussion<br />7:50-8:15 pm Presentation (At least two members of each table are invited, 2 mins / each member)<br />8:15-8:45 pm Session 2 discussion<br />8:45-9:00 pm Presentation<br /><br />------------------------------------------</span> <img class="smilies" src="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/images/smilies/icon_redface.gif" alt=":oops:" title="Embarrassed" /> <br /><br />Session I<br /><br />Three Common Bedtime Habits Destroying Your Sleep<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://elemental.medium.com/3-common-bedtime-habits-destroying-your-sleep-a4f5fe5e4c08">https://elemental.medium.com/3-common-b ... f5fe5e4c08</a><!-- m --><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">1. How is your sleep quality?  Please rate your sleep quality on a rating scale of 1-10, where 1 is “very poor” and 10 is “very good”.<br /><br />2. In your opinion, what is high-quality sleep?  Is quantity important?  How many hours do you usually sleep per day?<br /><br />3. How do you get a good night’s sleep?  Please share some smart habits that improve sleep quality, and some habits that destroy it.<br /></span><br /><br /><br />Session II<br /><br />Night owls and early birds have different personality traits<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.cbsnews.com/news/night-owls-and-early-birds-have-different-personality-traits/">https://www.cbsnews.com/news/night-owls ... ty-traits/</a><!-- m --><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">1. Are you an early bird (or a lark) or night owl?  Or something in-between? What time do you usually go to sleep and wake up?  Do you take a nap in the daytime?<br /><br />2. Do you know any “die-hard” late risers or early risers?  Do they have different personality traits?  Do you believe sleep habits make a difference on personality, intelligence, and/or success rate?<br /><br />3. Can our sleep habits be changed?  Do you believe our inner body clock is ruled by our genetics?  Is it possible to make the shift from evening people to morning people (or the opposite)?<br /></span><br />Agenda<br />6:30-7:15 pm Free talk<br />7:15-7:50 pm Session 1 discussion<br />7:50-8:15 pm Presentation (At least two members of each table are invited, 2 mins / each member)<br />8:15-8:45 pm Session 2 discussion<br />8:45-9:00 pm Presentation<br /><br />P.S.<br />1.因聚會地點是在咖啡店內，所以有低消80元喔。<br />2.參加三次後，只要繳交500元，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />3.請帶著開放與熱情來參加自由的全英文會話聚會~<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=13721">morris</a> — Mon Nov 16, 2020 5:31 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
